{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Christer Clerwall (2014) revealed that algorithm-generated content is not necessarily distinguishable from content written by journalists.",
    "To develop the ability to distinguish between human-written and AI-generated texts, the editor should interact more with a chatbot interface and discover its way of generating responses.",
    "Absurdity from AI might be viewed as a failure from the perspective of a data scientist and a success from the point of view of a literary artist (Adema, 2017).",
    "It is not the artistic quality of the generated text that impresses people but the extent to which the result resembles human writing.",
    "This matches with the two approaches of AI results perception: \"human-centered\" and \"rationalist\" (Miroshnichenko, 2018)."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
